The paper introduces a new type of finite automata, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also examines the computational power of different versions of these automata, which involves analyzing their complexity and behavior, making it relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
